<TITLE> Ports told to raise Signal 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)-- Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mangla ports have been advised to raise local cautionary signal three as the sea will remain rough with weather remaining squally over the Bay. Met official Abdur Rahman told bdnews24.com on Tuesday evening because of the sea being rough over the north Bay, there is possibility of stormy wind blowing over the sea ports. All fishing boats and trawlers have been advised to remain close to the coast and not to venture into the sea until further notice. 
